Before writing, I should quickly verify the data types / number formats in columns B and C so I choose a compatible formula. Then I’ll replace the formula in column C with a blank-safe, midnight-safe version and apply it down all relevant rows.

A robust formula for this is:
`=IF(OR(A2="",B2=""),"",MOD(B2-TIME(0,30,0),1))`

- `MOD(...,1)` wraps negative times across midnight.
- `IF(OR(A2="",B2=""),"",...)` keeps C blank when the row has no usable input.

After that I’ll save to the output directory, recalculate, reload, and verify key cells including midnight-crossing rows and blank rows.
